Biography

2021-22 - Sophomore - Continued to hold a starting spot during her second season with the Captains, playing in 15 of CNU's 16 duals in the spring ... Ranked second on the team in singles victories with 10 including six at No. 3 ... Also went 6-6 in doubles action while playing primarily at No. 3 ... Paired with Karina Crivtonencu for a 4-2 record in doubles action ... Also appeared with three other partners during the year, picking up wins with Anna Campbell and Mia Linam ... Repeat selection to the C2C Academic All-Conference Team

2020-21 - Freshman - Stepped right into the starting lineup as a true freshman, playing in 13 of CNU's 14 total matches during the year ... Posted a 4-6 record in singles and a 6-7 record in doubles play in the shortened spring season ... Won three of her first four matches with victories against Sweet Briar, NC Wesleyan, and Southern Virginia ... Won four straight to start the year in doubles including an 8-5 win at No. 3 doubles against Division I Norfolk State ... Named to the Coast-To-Coast Athletic Conference All-Academic team

At Riverbend -- Three-time All-Area selection...Free-Lance Star Player of the Year as a junior...Won Region 6B singles title as a junior and reached finals in doubles...Named All-State as a junior and reached Class 6 State semifinals...Named team captain as a junior and senior...Helped lead team to district title in her first two seasons...Team reached regional tournament as a sophomore...Earned highest USTA ranking of 28 in Mid-Atlantic region for Girls 18 and under...Ranked number 4 in the Virginia class of 2020 by tennisrecruiting.net...Member of the National Honor Society.

Personal -- Kiersten Alexa Chang was born in Fredericksburg, Va...Daughter of Norman and Stephanie Chang...Has two sisters, Kendal and Caleigh...Favorite athletes are Roger Federer and Naomi Osaka...Person in history she'd most like to meet is Martin Luther King, Jr...Dream vacation is a trip to Hawaii...Favorite food is pizza...Favorite movie is The Proposal and favorite TV show is The Vampire Diaries...Favorite books are the Harry Potter series...Favorite musicians are Lauv and Bruno Mars...Majoring in Cellular, Molecular, and Physiological Biology (Pre-Med)
